credit.credit-words: O God, how often hath Thine ear

But, that my faith no more may know Or change, or interval, or end, Help me in all Thy paths to go, And now, as e'er, my voice attend, And gladden me with answers mild, And dwell, O Father, with Thy child!

direction-type.words: This day the covenant I sign,
The bond of sure and promised
Nor can I doubt its power divine,
That blood I take, that blood
